captions.text: [MUSIC PLAYING]
-Hi, guys.
It's Brooklyn.
-And it's Bailey.

And obviously, I
have some laryngitis.

So Brooklyn's going to be doing
most of the voiceovers today.

-And today we're going to be
doing a spring fashion video.

And we're excited
to show you all

of our new and improved fashion
for the upcoming spring.
[MUSIC PLAYING]

-For Bailey's number
one outfit, she's

going for more of a bright,
floral, summery look.

To start off, she's
got a gold braided

headband that she
got from Target.

It's more of a Roman
look, which is really in.

She also has a bright
pink floral scarf
that we got from Forever 21.

Bailey got her light pink
T-shirt from Forever 21.

And it's really
light and airy, which

is really good for
the warm weather.

She's wearing a bright pink
bow bracelet from Forever 21.

And bow bracelets are
really trending right now.
[MUSIC PLAYING]

-She's also wearing white
shorts from Old Navy.

They're the perfect length,
not too long, not too short.

So for summer,
they're really great.

Her brown belt is
from American Eagle.
It's a little old.

We got it a while ago,
but we love it anyway.
Her shoes are from Express.
They're really cute.
They're gladiator shoes.

And we love wearing them,
because they're airy,

but they're also really
cute for the warm weather.
[MUSIC PLAYING]

-My first outfit is
Coachella-inspired.

It's really a bohemian,
sweet, cute look,

which is really great
for the spring time.
[MUSIC PLAYING]
-My headband is from Forever 21.

It's a floral Coachella look,
because florals are really
in right now.
My necklace is a tribal pendant.

It's got little jade diamonds
in it that make it really cute.
My bracelets are from Target.

I'm just wearing two
of them on my one arm.

Not too much, but not
too little, either.
So it's the perfect amount.

My jean shorts are
from American Eagle.

The are the perfect
length as well.

They're not too short,
they're not too long.
They're just like a dark jean.
[MUSIC PLAYING]

-Again, we have more
gladiator shoes,

only these ones are black
and have more straps.
We got these from Target.

Target has the best
summer sandals.

So if you need any
sandals, go there.
[MUSIC PLAYING]
-Hey guys, it's Bailey.

And I'm going to try and do
this voiceover for this outfit.
So to start, we have my fedora.

And technically I got
this from my mom's closet,

because she a ton
of really cute hats.

But you can find fedoras
in Target, or basically
anywhere else.

For my shirt, there's a lot
of these wandering around all

over the place, but we
got this from Old Navy.

This is a really
simple jean shirt.
It goes with basically anything.

And then for my pants, we got
these again, from Old Navy.

They have the best
summer shorts ever.

And then my belt
came from Forever 21.

You can find a brown braided
belt basically anywhere.

So whatever you find
will probably work,
[MUSIC PLAYING]

-Our shoes, I know we got from
a friend as a hand-me-down.

But also I know for a fact that
she got those from Old Navy.

So if you guys find any that are
similar, I'm sure they'll work.
[MUSIC PLAYING]
-Hey guys.

For my second outfit,
I'm going for more of a
dressed up look/casual look.
So it's kind of in-between.

To start off, I brought my brown
braided headband from Claire's.

And we actually bought
it a little while ago,

but I'm pretty sure you
guys can find it anywhere.

My necklace is from
Dressing Your Truth.

And I actually stole it
from my mom's closet.
In case you're wondering.
My mom has lots of good clothes.
I borrow them sometime.

Overalls are really
trending right now.

We found this pair
of shortalls, I

think that's what they're
called when they're shorts.

We found this pair of
shortalls at American Eagle.

We found these
heels at Cheapskate,

which is a downtown
like, what is it called?
Thrift store.

And we used it in our
thrift store video.

So if you want to go check that
out, be sure to look at it.
[MUSIC PLAYING]

-For my third look,
I was trying to go

for more of a tribal
but dressy outfit that's

really simple for
the spring or summer.

Very first, I have a
pancaked braid on the side.
It's really loose.

And then I have
this denim jacket

that's kind of roughed up, but
that's the point of the jacket.
And it's from Love Culture.

I also have this
tribal print necklace.

It's kind of like an arrow,
bold, kind of pointing down.

And this necklace
is from Forever 21.
[MUSIC PLAYING]

My dress is from-- oh, let me
think for a second-- oh yeah.
It's from Love Culture as well.
And it's really flowy.

And then my bracelet
is from Forever 21.

My gold flats we
found at Target.

And I love these because
they're just super simple.

And they basically
match anything.
[MUSIC PLAYING]

-This is a really unique
style, but I really
love this outfit anyways.

I braided my hair
into a milk maid style
with little curls in the front.

My necklace is a black
butterfly on gold chains.
It is from Charming Charlie's.

It's a butterfly, so
it kind of matches
the summery feel to my outfit.
[MUSIC PLAYING]

I found my cream lace
over top at [? Bohme, ?]

but you can literally
find these everywhere.

I see them everywhere
at like, every store.

Because they're completely
trending right now.

My minty turquoise shorts
are from Old Navy as well.

Again, there the perfect
length for summer.
Not too long, not too short.
My shoes are from Payless.

They're really
simple, really pretty

much just black sandals
you can find anywhere.
[MUSIC PLAYING]

-I hope you guys enjoyed
our spring outfit video.

Feel free to leave a
comment below on which
outfit was your favorite.

-And we'll see you
guys next week.
Bye.
[MUSIC PLAYING]
